{
  "message": "test(conformance): add 11 infinity edge case fuzz seeds (testing-fuzzing)\n\nAdd structured corpus seeds for arithmetic operations with infinity:\n- mod_pos_div_pos_inf: 1.0 % inf = 1.0\n- mod_neg_div_pos_inf: -1.0 % inf = inf\n- mod_pos_div_neg_inf: 1.0 % -inf = -inf\n- mod_neg_div_neg_inf: -1.0 % -inf = -1.0\n- mod_zero_div_inf: 0.0 % inf = 0.0\n- mod_nan_div_inf: nan % inf = nan\n- floordiv_pos_div_inf: floor(1.0/inf) = 0.0\n- floordiv_neg_div_inf: floor(-1.0/inf) = -1.0\n- mul_inf_by_zero: inf * 0 = nan\n- div_by_neg_zero: 1.0 / -0.0 = -inf\n- add_inf_to_neg_inf: inf + (-inf) = nan\n\nThese seeds exercise the recently-fixed python_mod_f64 infinity handling\nand other IEEE-754 special cases.\n\nCloses cod1m04 (already implemented - info() has memory usage).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
